      "comment": "COMPTON BAKER (8) produced a modest effort most recently when fifth at this track over 400m behind Pure Gout (23.59) in a Grade 6. Was in the money prior to that. Good beginner but will need a little luck early crossing from an outside draw. Can make amends. ASTON DEUTZ (2) shapes well after a fast run last time, finishing second in a Grade 6 at this track in 23.16. Rates a leading chance if runs up to latest. LINDA LOU (5) recorded her best time this course and distance latest, finishing a 2.5 lengths third behind Pure Gout in 23.31. Has the ability and looks a key chance. BALI UNLEASHED (7) has ability and finds the right scenario to bounce back.",
